quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  17,105,We have sent it down with truth and with truth it has come down. We only sent you to bring good news and to give warning
  17,106,"We have divided up the Qur´an, so you can recite it to mankind at intervals, and We have sent it down little by little"
  17,107,"Say: ´Have iman in it or do not have iman in it.´ Certainly, when it is recited to them, those who were given knowledge before it fall on their faces in prostration"
  17,108,"saying, ´Glory be to our Lord! The promise of our Lord is truly fulfilled!´ Weeping"
  17,109,"they fall to the ground in prostration, and it increases them in humility"
  17,110,"Say: ´Call on Allah or call on the All-Merciful, whichever you call upon, the Most Beautiful Names are His.´ Do not be too loud in your salat or too quiet in it, but try to find a way between the two"
  17,111,"And say: ´Praise be to Allah Who has had no son and Who has no partner in His Kingdom and Who needs no one to protect Him from abasement.´ And proclaim His Greatness repeatedly"
  18,1,Praise belongs to Allah Who has sent down the Book to His slave and has put no crookedness in it
  18,2,"It is straight, to warn of violent force direct from Him, and to give the good news to the muminun, those who do right actions, that for them there is an excellent reward"
  18,3,a place in which they will remain for ever
  18,4,and to warn those who say ´Allah has a son.´